    examTip: "Inotrope selection in cardiogenic shock: Dobutamine (beta-1 agonist → cAMP PRODUCTION) — first-line but limited by receptor downregulation. Milrinone (PDE3i → blocks cAMP BREAKDOWN) — add when dobutamine insufficient, works independently of beta-receptors. BUT milrinone causes more hypotension (vasodilation) → may need vasopressor (norepinephrine) concurrently. Risk: both agents increase arrhythmia risk through Ca²⁺ overload (similar to digoxin toxicity). OPTIME-CHF: chronic milrinone → increased mortality — use SHORT-TERM only.",
