    stem: "A 48-year-old female with Raynaud's phenomenon secondary to systemic sclerosis develops progressive exertional dyspnea. RHC confirms WHO Group 1 PAH (mPAP 48 mmHg, PCWP 12 mmHg, PVR 9 Wood units). Her rheumatologist starts ambrisentan and tadalafil (dual oral therapy). What are the specific vascular targets, and why is combination therapy more effective than monotherapy?",
