    examTip: "PAH pathway-targeted therapy: ENDOTHELIN → ambrisentan (selective ETA), bosentan/macitentan (dual ETA+ETB). Hepatotoxicity: bosentan (monthly LFTs) > macitentan > ambrisentan (rare). NO-cGMP → tadalafil, sildenafil (PDE5i), riociguat (sGC stimulator — do NOT combine riociguat with PDE5i → hypotension). PROSTACYCLIN → epoprostenol (IV, continuous, most potent), treprostinil, iloprost, selexipag (oral). Combination therapy now standard: initial dual (AMBITION) or triple for high-risk. Pregnancy: ALL ERAs are TERATOGENIC — mandatory pregnancy testing monthly.",
