    examTip: "Anticoagulation in valvular disease: MECHANICAL VALVES → warfarin ONLY (INR 2.5-3.5 for mitral, 2.0-3.0 for aortic bileaflet with no other risk factors). BIOPROSTHETIC VALVES → warfarin × 3-6 months post-surgery, then can consider DOAC or aspirin. AF WITH VALVULAR DISEASE: 'Valvular AF' (mechanical valve or moderate-severe MS) → warfarin. All other 'non-valvular AF' → DOACs preferred over warfarin (RE-LY, ROCKET-AF, ARISTOTLE, ENGAGE). DOACs are CONTRAINDICATED in: mechanical heart valves, moderate-severe mitral stenosis.",
