    stem: "A 60-year-old male with resistant hypertension (BP 168/98 on lisinopril 40mg, amlodipine 10mg, chlorthalidone 25mg) has aldosterone-to-renin ratio (ARR) of 42 (elevated), confirming primary aldosteronism. His NP adds spironolactone. What is the pathophysiological basis for aldosterone-driven resistant hypertension, and why is MRA therapy specifically effective?",
