    stem: "A 52-year-old female with Prinzmetal (variant) angina presents with recurrent early-morning chest pain with transient ST elevation that resolves spontaneously. Her NP prescribes amlodipine and sublingual nitroglycerin PRN. What is the specific pathophysiology of Prinzmetal angina, and why are beta-blockers (standard for typical angina) potentially HARMFUL?",
